        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Note: &lt;/b&gt;">For each master page used in your FrameMaker documents, a corresponding page layout is automatically created in your Flare project. You can use the page layouts to configure pages for print-based output<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Page_Layouts/About_Page_Layouts.htm">About Page Layouts</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../Page_Layouts/Editing_Pages_and_Frames.htm">Editing Pages and Frames</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. You can then create chapter breaks for your print-based output and assign these page layouts to the different topics in the output<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Output/Printed_Output/More_About_Printed_Output/Specifying_Chapter_Breaks_for_Printed_Output.htm">Specifying Chapter and Page Layout Breaks</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
